title: CNBC Daily Open: The FOMO momentum
description: Major U.S. indexes closed lower Friday. Despite that, indexes hit major market milestones last week, a testament to the rally’s current strength.

title: This 1-minute practice can help you 'break up with your phone,' says author who wrote the book on it
description: In her book "How to Break Up With Your Phone," Catherine Price goes into actionable practices that can help you curb your phone usage.

title: 'The Flash,' 'Elemental' disappoint as 'Spider-Verse' continues box office domination
description: Warner Bros.' "The Flash" and Disney and Pixar's "Elemental" disappointed during their box office debuts while Sony's "Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse" soared.

title: How 'Elemental' star Leah Lewis handles rejection and imposter syndrome in Hollywood
description: Leah Lewis discusses the best career lessons she's learned so far, and what she hopes audiences take away from her new Pixar feature.

title: I'm taking Harvard's free 6-week course on happiness—here's what I hope to learn
description: I'm taking a free, six-week Harvard course about happiness. These are some of the questions I hope to have answered by its end.

title: Nike's approach to solving the biggest problem for girls in sports
description: Girls are dropping out of sports at 'alarming rates' when they hit puberty, and Nike CEO John Donahoe says the research shows more female coaches would help.

title: Now Boarding: Here's what you need to know about flying in turbulence
description: On this episode of "Now Boarding," CNBC discusses turbulence we experience on airplanes and why it's usually nothing to worry about.

title: 'People just want their jets.' Paris Air show returns as Boeing, Airbus race to increase production
description: Aviation data firm IBA expects about 2,100 airplane orders at the Paris Air Show.

title: Blinken meets Chinese Foreign Minister Qin Gang on high-stakes diplomatic trip to Beijing
description: The trip by Blinken makes him the highest-level American official to visit China since Joe Biden became U.S. president.
